data.description: Location, location, location! Are you looking for a home convenient to Orlando International Airport, Downtown Orlando or Orlando Health?! Then look no further! Sitting on a massive corner lot at exactly a quarter of an acre, this home offers a side-entry garage and attractive curb appeal. Stepping through the front door you enter into a foyer with updated laminate flooring with the laminate carrying into the kitchen which is to your immediate right. The kitchen features a newer stainless-steel range (2017), dishwasher (2017) and microwave (2022). Featuring a space for a breakfast nook or a coffee bar, the kitchen has loads of natural light that filters in, keeping the space airy and bright. Off of the kitchen is an entry door that leads out to the 2-car garage, making it easy to unload groceries right from your car. You’ll also find laundry amenities, making weekend chores easy. Around the corner from the kitchen is a dining room/living room combo that can easily accommodate friends and family for holiday dinners and entertaining. The original terrazzo floors are in fantastic condition and help to cut down on cooling costs throughout the home. Crown-moulding, tall baseboards and shutters provide classic elements to the room, while the windows and door to the backyard once again help to fill the space with natural lighting. Speaking of the backyard, the living room opens up to a fantastic screen-enclosed patio space where you can comfortably continue your entertaining. Beyond that lies a big fenced-in backyard with loads of opportunity and lush greenery. Back inside, all three bedrooms are found down the hall, including the primary with its own ensuite and walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms are ideal for kiddos and guests, or as a home office or hobby room. A roomy 3-piece hall bath with a tub/shower combo is accessible to all. Additional upgrades to this home include a recently installed fence (2020) and a new roof (2020) which offers tons of peace of mind! This property is within close proximity to area dining, shopping and entertainment while the highly-sought Pershing K-8 is a stone’s throw away, with Boone High (Go Braves!) being just a 5-minute drive away! Don’t miss out on your opportunity to own in the Conway/SODO area—this great home is sure to go fast!
